dc:description{Literal}: France (1000070) 'member of' North Atlantic Treaty Organization (7029610);

rdf:value{Literal}@en: Area inhabited by Lower Paleolithic; Celt-speaking Gauls dominated by 5th century BCE; part of Roman Empire 125 BCE-5th century, then under Frankish influence; lost land to England 12th-16th centuries; monarchy fell in Revolution 1792; recurring expansion 16-19th centuries; official language is French, though Provençal, Breton, Flemish, Catalan, Corsican, Basque, and Germanic regional patois are also spoken.

rdfs:comment{Literal}: name may also be used to refer to ancient region larger than modern France
